  "description": "Use this skill when writing or debugging SOQL relationship queries in Apex \u2014 child-to-parent dot notation traversal, parent-to-child subqueries, and polymorphic TYPEOF lookups. Trigger keywords: relationship query, subquery, dot notation, getSObjects, TYPEOF, WhatId, WhoId. NOT for aggregate queries (use apex-aggregate-queries), NOT for SOSL text search, NOT for Bulk API data loads (subqueries unsupported there).",
  "file_location": "skills/apex/apex-soql-relationship-queries",
  "id": "apex/apex-soql-relationship-queries",
  "inputs": [
    "Object names and the relationship direction needed (child-to-parent or parent-to-child)",
    "Whether any lookup field is polymorphic (Task.WhatId, Task.WhoId, Event.WhatId, Event.WhoId, FeedItem.ParentId)",
    "API version in use (subqueries require API v58.0+; Bulk API excludes subqueries)"
  ],
